default 
defaultWe
default employ a “learn-by-doing
default” approach that challenges students to move beyond theory and to engage in hands-on activities. Students are 
defaulttaught
default 
defaultto think big while working together on real
default-world
default projects with leading companies. The program comprises two stages: 1) the Student Program 
defaultwhich runs in parallel to high school over the course of three years; and 2) the Alumni Program, which ensures the achievement of MEET’s long-term mission. The entire program incorporates a values-based ‘Deeper Understanding’ curriculum focused on dialogue
default and conflict resolution.
defaultStudent Recruitment
default7
default. The selection of participants is comprised of a 
defaultsix
default-month recruitment process that engages 
defaultPalestinian and Israeli
default 
defaulthigh school
default students 
defaultand identifies the top candidates to participate in the three-year prog
defaultram, ensuring equal representation of Israelis and Palestinians; males and females. Students are recruited from over 40 high schools from East and West Jerusalem, Ramallah, Bethlehem, Mevesseret, Beit Shemesh, Nazareth and more
default, engaging the OPT population
defaults central to the Conflict Pool
default. Applicants undergo a rigorous selection process, including a written exam, a group dynamics session and a personal interview. As an excellence 
defaultmodel, admittance is highly competitive (in 2013, 999 students applied while MEET
default only accepted 70 participants). All students receive a full scholarship, regardless of 
defaultsocio-economic background
default.
