default10
default. Teamwork is one of the primary tools in the program’s work model and its main objective is to encourage 
defaultcollaboration
default between students from different groups. The integration between Israelis an
defaultd Palestinians poses a chall
defaultenge for most students
default, as it requires them to contend with contradicting opinions and even carry out decisions taken by the group that run contrary to their own preferences. The most successful teams are usually those that have
default talked through the difficulties and have undergone a mutual process from beginning to end. Evaluations demonstrate that the degree of cooperation substantially increases with familiarity and experience. Dealing with these challenges is a significant educa
defaulttional and personal process for students. Throughout the course, 
defaultparticipants learn how to contend with opinions and positions that are different, at times even contradictory, to their own, to conduct themselves as a group that affords equal importance to 
defaulta variety of opinions, and to move forward by 
defaultpersuading 
defaultothers
default to adopt a fresh viewpoint
default. Evaluations demonstrate that the longer students have been participating in the program, the more at ease they are working with members of other teams.
