defaultDeeper Und
defaulterstanding
default Curriculum
default11
default. In addition to the academic and professional components of the program, MEET has developed a ‘Deeper Understanding’ (DU) curriculum that focuses on promoting dialogue and conflict resolution. It is a 
defaultvalues-based education that teaches youth how to communicate and deal with different subjects, such as respect, 
defaultidentity 
defaultand “the other.”
default The main purpose of these sessions is to provide students with a framework where the
defaulty can express themselves openly
default, a
defaultnd to discuss the difficulties Israelis and Palestinians
default experience
default as a means of learning and attaining tools to deal with conflict situations in real life. It allows subjects and stress points that are naturally kept under the surface to become exposed i
defaultn order to equip the youth with tools to express themselves in relation to a complex situation
default, and 
defaultexpand their critical thinking abilities as a result of 
defaultencountering new
default 
defaultperspectives
default. The direct effect of the DU sessions is that they strengthen social c
defaultonnections between students, which allows them to expand the range of topics they are able to discuss to include deeper and more sensitive subjects of a social and political nature. DU encourages students to behave in a responsible and mature manner, decre
defaultases disciplinary issues, and fosters a more productive environment. 
default12
default. Evaluations reveal that the DU sessions have a positive influence on the relationship and soci
defaultal atmosphere within the group. 
defaultS
defaulttudents recognize that it is possible to speak, argue a
defaultnd disagree while still maintaining mutual respect and civilized discourse.
default One of the most important skills acquired through these sessions is the ability to properly convey a message so that it is clear and authentic, 
defaultand expressed
default in a respectful and no
defaultn-insulting manner. These skills are designed to help with interpersonal and inter-group conflicts, and to 
defaultcultivate 
defaulthabits
default that translate into personal and professional 
defaultnorms
default in their MEET teams, 
defaultalumni ventures, 
defaulthigher education, and eventually positions
default of leadership.
